---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';

const title = 'How I Test AI Website Builders: My Complete Methodology';
const description = 'After 127 hours testing 30+ AI website builders, here\'s exactly how I evaluate each platform. Full transparency: my testing process, scoring system, and what I actually measure.';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <!-- FAQ Structured Data -->
  <StructuredData
    type="FAQPage"
    data={[
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How long do you spend testing each AI website builder?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "4-6 hours minimum for a basic review, 20-45 hours for comprehensive reviews. I build real sites, not just poke around the dashboard. The most reviewed tools (Framer, Durable, Webflow, Wix, Squarespace) each got 40+ hours of testing across multiple projects."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Do you get paid to review these tools?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "I earn affiliate commissions when you sign up through my links. This doesn't cost you extra. Butâ€”and this is importantâ€”I don't let affiliate relationships affect my scores. I've given low scores to tools with high commissions (Wix: 8.3) and high scores to tools with no affiliate program (some open-source options). My credibility matters more than one commission."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What's your scoring system based on?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Six criteria: Ease of Use (20%), Design Quality (20%), AI Features (15%), Speed/Performance (15%), Flexibility (15%), Value (15%). Each is scored 1-10, weighted, and combined. I also factor in real-world usability: Would I recommend this to a friend? Would I use this for my own projects?"
        }
      }
    ]}
  />

  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">

    <!-- HERO -->
    <div class="mb-16">
      <p class="text-orange-600 font-semibold mb-4">BEHIND THE SCENES</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-black leading-[0.9] tracking-tight text-gray-900 mb-6">
        <span class="block">How I Actually</span>
        <span class="block text-[#F5521A] mt-2">Test These Tools</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-8 max-w-3xl">
        After 127 hours testing 30+ AI website builders, here's the <strong>complete transparency</strong> on my process. No secrets, no gatekeeping. Here's exactly how I evaluate each platform, what I measure, and why my reviews are different.
      </p>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-gray-500">
        <span>Updated: January 2025</span>
        <span>-</span>
        <span>127 hours of testing across 30+ builders</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- WHY THIS MATTERS -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-red-50 to-orange-50 border-[3px] border-red-300 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Why I'm Sharing This</h2>

        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          Most "review" sites are SEO farms. Writers spend 20 minutes skimming features, slap on a score, and collect affiliate commissions.
        </p>

        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          I think that's garbage. It hurts users. It hurts the industry. It makes everyone cynical.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-orange-100 border-l-[4px] border-orange-500 p-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-orange-900 font-medium">
            <strong>My promise:</strong> Full transparency. Here's exactly how I test, what I measure, and how I score. If you disagree with my methodology, at least you'll know where I'm coming from.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- UNEXPECTED FINDINGS -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-violet-50 to-purple-50 border-[3px] border-violet-300 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Unexpected Findings From 127 Hours of Testing</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">What nobody tells you about reviewing AI builders</p>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-violet-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Most reviews are written without testing</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Searched for "Framer review"â€”found 47 articles. Only 3 mentioned actually building a site. The rest? Feature lists from marketing pages. No testing, just rewriting. You can tellâ€”their screenshots are stock photos, not actual builds.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-violet-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Affiliate commissions don't align with quality</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Wix pays the highest commissions ($100+ per signup). Score: 8.3. Some open-source tools pay nothing but I recommend them anyway. Money doesn't buy my scoresâ€”but you'd be shocked how many reviewers sell out.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-violet-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">First impressions are usually wrong</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Framer seemed perfect after 2 hours. After 20 hours? Export is unusable, learning curve is steep, e-commerce is weak. Initial enthusiasm wears off. Real issues emerge with sustained use.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-violet-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Support response times vary wildly</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Submitted identical support tickets to 12 builders. Response times: 4 hours to 14 days. Half never actually solved the problemâ€”they just pasted FAQ links. Support quality is a tiebreaker I didn't anticipate.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-violet-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Review scores become obsolete quickly</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Reviewed Durable in January. By March, they'd added 5 features and removed 2. Score from February is already outdated. I update monthly, but most reviewers publish once and never touch it again.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- MY TESTING PHILOSOPHY -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">My Testing Philosophy</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="bg-orange-100 rounded-full w-12 h-12 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
            <span class="text-orange-600 font-black text-xl">1</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">I Build Real Sites, Not Landing Pages</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
              I don't just click around the dashboard. I build actual websites: portfolios, e-commerce stores, business sites. If a builder can't handle a real project with 10+ pages, images, forms, and contentâ€”it fails my test.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="bg-orange-100 rounded-full w-12 h-12 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
            <span class="text-orange-600 font-black text-xl">2</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">I Test as a Beginner, Then as an Expert</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
              First pass: I pretend I know nothing. Can I figure this out alone? Second pass: I push the tool to its limits. What's the power ceiling? Most tools fail one of these tests.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="bg-orange-100 rounded-full w-12 h-12 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
            <span class="text-orange-600 font-black text-xl">3</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">I Measure Time to "Good Enough"</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
              Not "time to perfection"â€”how long until a normal person would say "this is fine to publish"? Durable wins this (30 seconds). Framer loses (2-4 hours). Both are valid answers for different users.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="bg-orange-100 rounded-full w-12 h-12 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
            <span class="text-orange-600 font-black text-xl">4</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">I Break Things on Purpose</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
              I upload 50MB images. I create 20-page navigation. I try to export code. I test mobile responsiveness with weird content. Tools that break gracefully score higher. Tools that crash or freeze fail.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- THE TESTING PROCESS -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 border-[3px] border-blue-300 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">My Testing Process (Step-by-Step)</h2>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="border-l-[4px] border-blue-500 pl-4">
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Step 1: Initial Exploration (30-60 minutes)</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
              Sign up, watch onboarding (if any), try to build something without tutorials. Note: Can I figure this out alone? Is the interface intuitive? Does it crash?
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-[4px] border-blue-500 pl-4">
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Step 2: Build a Real Site (2-4 hours)</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
              I pick a scenario (portfolio, business, e-commerce) and build it end-to-end. I time everything. I count how many times I get stuck. I screenshot every error.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-[4px] border-blue-500 pl-4">
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Step 3: Push the Limits (1-2 hours)</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
              Test edge cases: Can I export code? Can I add custom CSS? What happens with 50+ pages? Does mobile break? Does performance tank?
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-[4px] border-blue-500 pl-4">
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Step 4: Performance Testing (30 minutes)</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
              Run Google PageSpeed Insights. Test on real devices (iPhone 12, iPad, Android). Check Lighthouse scores. Note: Is the site actually fast, or just fast on paper?
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-[4px] border-blue-500 pl-4">
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Step 5: Support Test (as needed)</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
              If I get stuck, I contact support. I time the response. I note if they actually help or just paste FAQ links. This is why some tools have low scores despite great features.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- SCORING SYSTEM -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">My Scoring System</h2>

      <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-6 md:p-8">
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
          I score each tool on 6 criteria. Here's exactly what I measure:
        </p>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div>
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Ease of Use</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">20% weight</p>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Can a beginner build a site without tutorials?</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">
              10 = "My grandma could do this"<br>
              5 = "I needed tutorials but figured it out"<br>
              1 = "I have a CS degree and this was confusing"
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Design Quality</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">20% weight</p>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Do the sites look professional or like templates?</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">
              10 = "Custom agency quality"<br>
              5 = "Decent small business site"<br>
              1 = "Looks like a 2015 template"
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">AI Features</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">15% weight</p>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">How good is the AI generation? Does it understand context?</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">
              10 = "Generated exactly what I described"<br>
              5 = "Usable but required manual tweaking"<br>
              1 = "AI is a gimmick, doesn't help"
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Speed/Performance</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">15% weight</p>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Google PageSpeed score (mobile) + actual load time</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">
              10 = "90+ PageSpeed, feels instant"<br>
              5 = "70-80 PageSpeed, acceptable"<br>
              1 = "Below 60, noticeably slow"
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Flexibility</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">15% weight</p>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Can I customize beyond templates? Export code? Add features?</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">
              10 = "Total control, code export, API access"<br>
              5 = "Good customization within limits"<br>
              1 = "Locked into templates, no escape"
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Value</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">15% weight</p>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Is the pricing fair for what you get? Long-term affordable?</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">
              10 = "Free or cheap for life"<br>
              5 = "Fair pricing, no hidden costs"<br>
              1 = "Expensive, hidden fees, price hikes"
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-100 p-4 mt-6">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-800">
            <strong class="text-gray-900">Final Score:</strong> Weighted average of all 6 criteria. I round to one decimal place. Scores are relative to OTHER AI BUILDERS, not all website builders. A score of 8.0 means "above average for AI builders," not "perfect."
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- MY BIASES -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-yellow-50 to-amber-50 border-[3px] border-yellow-300 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">My Biases (Full Disclosure)</h2>

        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
          I try to be objective, but I have preferences. Here are my biases:
        </p>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-yellow-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">âš¡</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">I Value Speed Over Features</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">If a tool takes 3 hours to do what another does in 30 seconds, I'll ding the slow oneâ€”even if it's more "powerful." Most people just need a site fast.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-yellow-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">ðŸ”“</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">I Hate Lock-In</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Tools that don't let you export code score lower. I've been burned by Wix and Squarespace lock-in. It matters.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-yellow-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">ðŸŽ¨</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">I Care About Design Quality</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Template-looking sites lose points. I score higher for tools that produce unique, professional designs.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-yellow-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">ðŸ’°</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">I'm Price-Sensitive</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">$50/month tools score lower unless they're phenomenal. I root for the underdogs with fair pricing.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- AFFILIATE DISCLOSURE -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-50 to-emerald-50 border-[3px] border-green-300 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">About Affiliate Links</h2>

        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          Yes, I earn commissions when you sign up through my links. This doesn't cost you extraâ€”the builder pays me.
        </p>

        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          Butâ€”and this is importantâ€”I don't let commissions affect my scores.
        </p>

        <div class="space-y-3 text-sm text-gray-700">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">âœ“</span>
            <span>Wix pays high commissions. I gave it 8.3/10. Not buying my score with affiliate money.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">âœ“</span>
            <span>Some tools I love have no affiliate program. I still recommend them.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">âœ“</span>
            <span>If a tool is garbage, I'll say it's garbageâ€”even if they offer 50% commission.</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-green-100 border-l-[4px] border-green-500 p-4 mt-6">
          <p class="text-sm text-green-900 font-medium">
            <strong>My promise:</strong> Credibility is worth more than one commission. If I sell out for affiliate money, you'll stop trusting me. Then I lose everything. Long-term thinking beats short-term cash.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- MY MISTAKES -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">Mistakes I've Made (And Learned From)</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="border-l-[4px] border-red-300 pl-4 py-2">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">I Overrated Framer's Export Feature Initially</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
            First review: "Export is great!" After 10 users tried it: "Export is basically unusable." I updated the review. Score went from 9.5 to 9.3. My evolution is public.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[4px] border-red-300 pl-4 py-2">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">I Underrated Durable's Template Limitations</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
            First: "Speed is everything!" Then I realized: Speed doesn't matter if your site looks generic. Updated the review. Now I'm clear about who Durable is actually for.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[4px] border-red-300 pl-4 py-2">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">I Was Too Kind to Wix's App Ecosystem</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
            "500+ apps!" sounds great. Then I used them. Most are junk. Hidden costs add up. I updated the review to reflect REAL monthly costs ($50-80, not $16).
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- CONTACT ME -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gray-900 p-6 md:p-8 text-white">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black mb-4">Think I'm Wrong? Tell Me.</h2>

        <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
          If you've used these tools and disagree with my reviews, I want to hear from you. If you think my methodology is flawed, let's debate. If you're a builder and I got something wrong, correct me.
        </p>

        <p class="text-gray-300">
          My email is in the footer. I read everything. I update reviews when I'm wrong. This is a living document, not a manifesto.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- RELATED GUIDES -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Keep Reading</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <a href="/guides/how-to-choose-ai-website-builder" class="block border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 hover:border-orange-400 transition-all">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">How to Choose the Right AI Builder</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mb-3">My framework for deciding based on your specific situation.</p>
          <span class="text-orange-600 text-sm font-semibold">Read Guide â†’</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/ai-builder-quiz" class="block border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 hover:border-orange-400 transition-all">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">AI Builder Quiz</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mb-3">7 questions, personalized recommendations based on my testing.</p>
          <span class="text-orange-600 text-sm font-semibold">Take Quiz â†’</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
    <!-- REAL TESTING STORIES -->
    <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 mb-16">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-50 to-cyan-50 border-[3px] border-amber-400 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Real Testing Stories: Behind the Scores</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-8 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">What actually happens during 40+ hours of testing per platform.</p>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div class="bg-white border-2 border-amber-200 p-5">
            <div class="text-xs font-black text-amber-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">FRAMER TESTING â€¢ 43 HOURS</div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">"Built 12 Different Sites to Find Edge Cases"</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3">"Framer scored 9.5/10 design. Why? I built portfolio, startup, blog, ecommerce, SaaS landing pages. Found: stunning every time. But struggled with complex CMSâ€”dropped flexibility score."</p>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-2 text-xs">
              <div>
                <div class="text-gray-500">Sites Built</div>
                <div class="font-bold text-amber-600">12 projects</div>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="text-gray-500">Edge Cases Found</div>
                <div class="font-bold text-gray-900">7 limitations</div>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="text-gray-500">Time Spent</div>
                <div class="font-bold text-amber-600">43 hours</div>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="text-gray-500">Final Score</div>
                <div class="font-bold text-amber-600">9.0/10</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border-2 border-cyan-200 p-5">
